Drift's visual identity is configurable, not hardcoded. Different users have different terminals (dark vs light backgrounds, specific color schemes), different aesthetic preferences (minimal vs vibrant), and different accessibility needs (color blindness). A theming system with 14 independently-configurable elements lets each user get output that works for them without modifying drift's source code. Themes are selectable at runtime via --theme=NAME or fully overridden via .drift/theme.xml. The guardrail property (<ref spec="output.guardrail_property">guardrail</ref>) holds for every theme. See <ref spec="open_source_tools_drift.dual_audience_constraint">the dual audience constraint</ref> and <ref spec="output.theme_system">the theme system</ref>.